article.headline: Xavier 69, Marshall 46
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Justin Doellman set career highs of 22 points and nine rebounds to lead Xavier to a 69-46 victory over Marshall on Thursday night. Doellman also made a career-best five 3-pointers in nine attempts as the Musketeers (5-4) won their third consecutive game. Stanley Burrell scored 13 points and Justin Cage added 10 for Xavier. The Thundering Herd (2-7) had their lowest scoring output this season while losing for the sixth time in seven games. Joe Miles led the Thundering Herd with 14 points, continuing his streak of scoring in double figures in every game this season. Lavar Carter added 10 points. Marshall never got closer than nine points in the second half, the last time coming at the 10:47 mark. Doellman made three 3s after that, helping Xavier close the game on a 27-13 run. It was the Thundering Herd's worst loss of the season, eclipsing a 89-69 setback against Oregon. Marshall led 13-12 with 11:54 left in the first half, but Xavier went on a 13-2 to take a 25-15 halftime lead. Xavier limited the Thundering Herd to 17 shots in the first half by forcing 13 turnovers. It was the teams' first meeting since the 1975-76 season.
